content: Caught up with some old friends from NYU. They're all into different tech startups now. Makes me wonder if I should start something myself.
Setup my new workstation with a Japanese aesthetic. Minimalism and functionality, like the perfect algorithm.
Had a thought: If life's a simulation, maybe we're all just trading different currencies of experience.
Debating between diving deeper into quant trading or exploring digital consciousness. What's more impactful, the market or the mind?
Found an old sketchbook from college. Might start sketching again, blend some art into my tech world.
Had a dream I was coding in a temple. When I woke up, I had a new idea for a smart contract. Reality or simulation?
Thinking about the intersection of blockchain and space commerce. Could we trade resources from space? Maybe I'll simulate this in my next project.
Visited a local tech meetup. Got some advice on quantum computing applications in trading. Exciting and overwhelming.
Mom called. She's proud but worried about my health. "Balance your screen time with some real time," she says. Always the philosopher.
Reflecting on my Japan trip. The blend of tradition and technology there... it's like a blueprint for my career.
Just realized, my code from last night has a Japanese influence. Subconscious integration at its finest.
Looking at the city lights from my apartment. NYC's energy is back, but with a new perspective. Maybe it's time to start a new chapter.
